$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'E mafai ona e fa&#39;aogaina le hexadecimal e fa&#39;aliliu ai i le va o le numera ma le numera binary. Mo se fa&#39;ata&#39;ita&#39;iga, o le fa&#39;aliliuina o le 10011011001010 i le hexadecimal e maua ai le 0x4F. O lona uiga o le tau 4F o loʻo faʻatusalia le numera binary 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'I le matematika ma le faasaienisi komepiuta, o le hexadecimal (faʻavae 16, poʻo le hex) o se faiga numera tulaga ma se radix, poʻo le faʻavae, o le 16. E faʻaogaina ai le sefuluono faʻailoga maʻoti, o le tele o faʻailoga 0-9 e faʻatusalia ai le numera zero i le iva, ma le A, B, C, D, E, F (poʻo le isi a–f) e fai ma sui o le aofaʻi o le sefulu i le sefululima. Mo se fa&#39;ata&#39;ita&#39;iga, o le numera hexadecimal 2AF3 e tutusa, i le decimal, i le (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , poʻo le 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'O numera hexadecimal ta&#39;itasi e fai ma sui o numera binary e fa (fa&#39;aigoa o le &quot;nibble&quot;), ma o le fa&#39;aogaina muamua o le fa&#39;ailoga hexadecimal o se fa&#39;ata&#39;ita&#39;iga fa&#39;alelei a tagata o tau fa&#39;ailoga fa&#39;akomepiuta i komepiuta ma fa&#39;aeletonika numera. Mo se fa&#39;ata&#39;ita&#39;iga, e mafai ona va&#39;ava&#39;ai le tau o byte mai le 0 i le 255 (decimal) ae atonu e sili atu ona fa&#39;atusaina o ni numera hexadecimal e lua ile va 00 e o&#39;o ile FF. O le Hexadecimal e masani ona faʻaaogaina e fai ma sui o tuatusi komepiuta.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex o se fa&#39;apuupuuga o le Hexadecimal, lea e fa&#39;avae i luga o le fa&#39;avae -16 fausaga ma fa&#39;aoga mo le fa&#39;afaigofieina o fa&#39;atonuga i komepiuta. O lenei 16 fa&#39;ailoga numera faiga na atiaʻe e avea o se auala e faʻalavelave ai se numera binary 8-bit, ina ia mafai ona faʻaogaina faʻamatalaga i komepiuta e aunoa ma se taumafaiga. E mafai ona lolomi ma lolomi e fa&#39;aaoga ai numera hex eseese e lua ma numera hex ta&#39;itasi e fa&#39;aalia ai se nibble po&#39;o se fa&#39;asologa 4-bits.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'O lenei faiga numera e fa&#39;aogaina ai fa&#39;ailoga e 16 o lo&#39;o fa&#39;atusalia i se laina mai le 0-9 po&#39;o le AF. O le 0–9 o lo&#39;o fa&#39;atusalia ai numera e o&#39;o atu i le iva ae o le AF o lo&#39;o fa&#39;atusaina e le numera 10-15. Pe a faatusatusa i isi ituaiga e tolu o faiga numera, o le faiga numera hexadecimal e manatu e sili ona aoga.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'E le aoga lau code hexadecimal';
